stow: stow (Manages installation process)
stow:
stow: Manages the installation process by keeping packages separate while
stow: making them appear to be installed in the same place. Stow doesn't
stow: store an extra state between runs, so there's no danger of mangling
stow: directories when file hierarchies don't match the database. Also,
stow: stow will never delete any files, directories, or links that appear in
stow: a stow directory, so it is always possible to rebuild the target tree.
stow:
